  "htmlText": "<!-- \nA simple navlist using built-in styles that should be touch friendly. \nWe are also using Font Awesome here and in a few buttons for icons\n-->\n<ul class=\"tnavlist\">\n    <li class=\"tnavli\"><a class=\"tnava\" onclick=\"showMain();\" href=\"javascript:void(0)\"><i class=\"fa fa-home\"></i> Home</a></li>\n    <li class=\"tnavli\"><a class=\"tnava\" onclick=\"alertify.log('News');\" href=\"javascript:void(0)\">News</a></li>\n    <li class=\"tnavli\"><a class=\"tnava\" onclick=\"alertify.log('Contact');\" href=\"javascript:void(0)\">Contact</a></li>\n    <li class=\"tnavli\"><a class=\"tnava\" onclick=\"showAbout();\" href=\"javascript:void(0)\"><i class=\"fa fa-info-circle\"></i> About</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- wrapping most of this UI into this Main Div (Home on navlist -->\n<div id=\"divMain\">\n    <br/>\n    <span style=\"color:#ff9\"><i>This demo relies on a new stylesheet created for TridentSandbox as well as \n        a new script for the TridentList you see two of.  Both are automatically included, \n        so that you can use similarly to how this sample uses them.</i></span>\n    <br/><br/>\n\n    <table width=\"100%\">\n        <tr>\n            <td valign='top'>\n                <ul id=\"demoListView\" class=\"tlist\"></ul>\n            </td>\n            <td valign='top'>\n                <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"getId()\">Get ID</button><br/><br/>\n                <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"deleteItem()\"><i class=\"fa fa-trash-o\"></i> Delete</button><br/><br/>\n                <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"addItem()\"><i class=\"fa fa-plus\"></i> Add</button><br/><br/>\n                <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"editItem()\"><i class=\"fa fa-pencil-square-o\"></i> Edit</button>\n            </td>\n            <td valign='top'>\n                <ul id=\"demoListView2\" class=\"tlist\"></ul>\n            </td>\n            <td valign='top'>\n                <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"getId2()\">Get ID</button><br/><br/>\n                <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"deleteItem2()\"><i class=\"fa fa-trash-o\"></i> Delete</button>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <br/>\n    <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"changeMenuColor()\">Change Menu Color</button>\n    <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"changeListCaptionColor()\">Change List Caption Color</button>\n    <button class=\"shiny-blue\" onclick=\"makeListsBright()\">Make List Bright</button>\n\n    <h3 style=\"color:#ff9\">Button Styles</h3>\n    <button class=\"shiny-blue\">shiny-blue</button>\n    <button class=\"minimal\">minimal</button>\n    <button class=\"thoughtbot\">thoughtbot</button>\n    <button class=\"purple-candy\">purple-candy</button>\n    <button class=\"cupid-green\">cupid-green</button>\n    <button class=\"cupid-blue\">cupid-blue</button>\n    <button class=\"blue-pill\">blue-pill</button>\n    <button class=\"download-itunes\">download-itunes</button>\n    <button class=\"skip\">skip</button>\n    <button class=\"minimal-indent\">minimal-indent</button>\n    <button>default</button>\n\n    <h3 style=\"color:#ff9; padding:4px\">Checkbox Styles</h3>\n\n    <!-- \nThe CSS Checkboxes we are using are somewhat particular about sizing.\nIt is recommended that you use an HTML table for layout similar to below \n-->\n\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">slideOne: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"slideOne\">\t\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"slideOne\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"slideOne\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">slideTwo: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"slideTwo\">\t\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"slideTwo\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"slideTwo\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">slideThree: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"slideThree\">\t\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"slideThree\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"slideThree\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n\n    <!-- second row of checkboxes, using multiple tables just for simplification of each set -->\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">roundedOne: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"roundedOne\">\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"roundedOne\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"roundedOne\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">roundedTwo: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"roundedTwo\">\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"roundedTwo\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"roundedTwo\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n\n    <!-- third row of checkboxes -->\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">squaredOne: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"squaredOne\">\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"squaredOne\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"squaredOne\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">squaredTwo: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td>\n                <div class=\"squaredTwo\">\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"squaredTwo\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"squaredTwo\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n    <br/>\n\n    <!-- fourth row of checkboxes -->\n    <span style=\"color:#ddd\"><i>If you use the following you may need fixed width column for checkbox :</i></span>\n    <table>\n        <tr>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">squaredThree: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td width=\"60px\">\n                <div class=\"squaredThree\">\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"squaredThree\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"squaredThree\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n            <td width=\"20px\">&nbsp;</td>\n            <td>\n                <span style=\"color:#ddd\">squaredFour: </span>\n            </td>\n            <td width=\"60px\">\n                <div class=\"squaredFour\">\n                    <input class=\"cssdeck\" type=\"checkbox\" value=\"None\" id=\"squaredFour\" name=\"check\" />\n                    <label for=\"squaredFour\"></label>\n                </div>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    </table>\n\n    <!-- Other options for checkboxes and radio buttons -->\n\n    <h3 style=\"color:#ff9\">Radio Buttons</h3>\n    <span style=\"color:#ddd\">Click radio buttons to select:</span> \n    <br/><br/>\n    <input class=\"vpatel\" type=\"radio\" id=\"radio1\" name=\"radios\" value=\"all\" checked>\n    <label for=\"radio1\">iPhone</label>\n    <input class=\"vpatel\" type=\"radio\" id=\"radio2\" name=\"radios\"value=\"false\">\n    <label for=\"radio2\">Galaxy S IV</label>\n    <input class=\"vpatel\" type=\"radio\" id=\"radio3\" name=\"radios\" value=\"true\">\n    <label for=\"radio3\">Nexus S</label>\n\n    <br><br>\n    <span style=\"color:#ddd\">Click checkboxes to select: </span><br/><br/>\n    <input class=\"vpatel\" type=\"checkbox\" id=\"chk1\" name=\"chk\" value=\"all\" checked>\n    <label for=\"chk1\">iPhone</label>\n    <input class=\"vpatel\" type=\"checkbox\" id=\"chk2\" name=\"chk\"value=\"false\">\n    <label for=\"chk2\">Galaxy S IV</label>\n    <input class=\"vpatel\" type=\"checkbox\" id=\"chk3\" name=\"chk\" value=\"true\">\n    <label for=\"chk3\">Nexus S</label>\n</div> \n\n<div id=\"divAbout\" style=\"display:none\">\n    <p style=\"color:#ddd\">This sample demonstrates how you might utilize a variety of control styles added \n        recently to TridentSandbox to implement a touch-friendly interface using Trident Sandbox. </p>\n\n    <p style=\"color:#ddd\">This sample depends on styles defined in sandbox.css as well as \n        the TridentList control defined in tridentlist.js, so if portability to non TridentSandbox \n        environments is important to you, you might want to stick to stock html controls or \n        dig into the files mentioned to extract relevant styles/javascript.</p>\n</div>\n\n",
  "scriptText": "// Set page background color\nsandbox.ui.setBackgroundColor(\"#444\");\n\n// Set up a callback to handle TridentList item selection events\nfunction listCallback(sender, id) {\n    alertify.log(\"sender : \" + sender + \"; id : \" + id);\n}\n\n// some generic event handlers to show interfacing with TridentList\nfunction getId() { alertify.log(tlv.listSettings.selectedId); }\nfunction deleteItem() { tlv.deleteListItem(); }\nfunction addItem() {\n    var caption = \"\", desc = \"\";\n\n    alertify.prompt(\"Enter caption\", function (e, str) {\n        if (e) {\n            caption = str;\n\n            alertify.prompt(\"Enter description\", function (e, str) {\n                if (e) {\n                    desc = str;\n\n                    // first param (id) doesn't have to be number, \n                    // we will just use caption since we dont have \n                    // loki or TridentDB to generate new numeric ones\n                    tlv.addListItem(caption, caption, desc);\n                }\n            });\n        } \n    });\t\n}\nfunction editItem() {\n    var caption = \"\", desc = \"\";\n\n    alertify.prompt(\"Enter caption\", function (e, str) {\n        if (e) {\n            caption = str;\n\n            alertify.prompt(\"Enter description\", function (e, str) {\n                if (e) {\n                    desc = str;\n                    tlv.updateListItem(tlv.listSettings.selectedId, caption, desc);\n                }\n            });\n        } \n    });\t\n}\n\n// Buttons to manipulate second TridentList control\n// Mostly to prove control internally maps correctly across multiple lists\nfunction getId2() {\talertify.log(tlv2.listSettings.selectedId); }\nfunction deleteItem2() { tlv2.deleteListItem(); }\n\n// override style for navlist background color\nfunction changeMenuColor() {\n    $(\"ul.tnavlist\").css(\"background-color\", \"#228\");\n    $(\"a.tnava\").css(\"background-color\", \"#228\");\n\n    // override hover highlight\n    $(\"a.tnava\").mouseenter(function() {\n        $(this).css(\"background\", \"#F00\").css(\"background-color\", \"#44b\");\n    }).mouseleave(function() {\n        $(this).css(\"background\", \"00F\").css(\"background-color\", \"#228\");\n    });\n}\n\n// Override style to change the list caption color only\nfunction changeListCaptionColor() {\n    tlv.setCaptionColor(\"#484\");\n}\n\n// Overrides styles to make all Trident Lists in this page load bright\nfunction makeListsBright() {\n    tlv.makeBright();\n}\n\n// navbar event handler\nfunction showMain() {\n    $(\"#divAbout\").hide();\n    $(\"#divMain\").show();\n}\n\n// navbar event handler\nfunction showAbout() {\n    $(\"#divMain\").hide();\n    $(\"#divAbout\").show();\n}\n\n// Create the TridentList which converts a UL defined in markup to a styled list\n// with additional functionality.\nvar tlv = new TridentList(\"demoListView\", listCallback);\ntlv.clearList();\ntlv.addListItem(1, \"Test One\", \"Test One Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(2, \"Test Two\", \"Test Two Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(3, \"Test Three\", \"Test Three Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(4, \"Test Four\", \"Test Four Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(5, \"Test Five\", \"Test Five Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(6, \"Test Six\", \"Test Six Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(7, \"Test Seven\", \"Test Seven Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(8, \"Test Eight\", \"Test Eight Description\");\ntlv.addListItem(9, \"Test Nine\", \"Test Nine Description\");\n\n// Create a second TridentList with different control id but same callback.\n// you can use separate callbacks for each list if you want, or handle all of \n// them in a single handler as is done here.\n\n// In this second Trident List we also use some methods for constructing our html\n// content within each item.  Each item can have their own style but ideally you would\n// style all of them similarly instead of as we are doing here\nvar tlv2 = new TridentList(\"demoListView2\", listCallback);\ntlv2.clearList();\ntlv2.addListItemRaw(1, \"<label style='display:inline-block; color:#fff; width:30px'><i class='fa fa-exclamation-circle'></i></label><label style='display:inline-block; width:100px; color:#8a8'>Test2 One</label><span style='color:#88a'>Test2 One Description</span>\");\ntlv2.addListItem(2, \"Test2 Two\", \"Test2 Two Description\");\ntlv2.addListItemRaw(3, \"<table><tr><td width=30><div style='display:inline-block; background-color:#b44; width:25px; height:35px;'></div></td><td><label style='color:#ddd; font-size:20px'>Click Me :&nbsp </label></td><td><button class='skip' onclick='alertify.success(\\\"hello\\\")'>Test2 3</button></td>\");\ntlv2.addListItem(4, \"Test2 Four\", \"Test2 Four Description\");\n\n// passing a fourth option param (isDescHtml) designates the third param is HTML encoded\ntlv2.addListItem(5, \"Test2 Five\", \"<u><i>Test2</i></u> <label style='color:#8a8'>Five Description</label>\", true);\ntlv2.addListItem(6, \"Test2 Six\", \"Test2 Six Description\");\ntlv2.addListItem(7, \"Test2 Seven\", \"Test2 Seven Description\");\ntlv2.addListItem(8, \"Test2 Eight\", \"Test2 Eight Description\");\ntlv2.addListItem(9, \"Test2 Nine\", \"Test2 Nine Description\");\n"
